#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textit{As dice roll and fortunes shift, the lands of Antagarich spread before you in all their splendor.\n"
"  Your destiny follows these celestial rolls, each battle and treasure determined by chance.\n"
"  Will you emerge victorious in this battle royale, claim the sacred grail, or stand alone as the king of the hill when the final die settles?  % no-check-caps\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Instead of playing a specific Scenario, you can follow these guidelines to create a random one.\n"
"Of course, you can adjust everything at will.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\subsection*{\\MakeUppercase{Scenario Type}}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Choose one of the following types for your play:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:26
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Free-for-All} -- Win by eliminating your opponents or gaining more Victory Points (VPs) than them.\n"
"VPs are counted in accordance to the Tournament book.\n"
"Additionally, you get:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item 5 VPs for flagging a Dragon Utopia for the first time.\n"
"  \\item 2 VPs for controlling the Dragon Utopia at the end of the game.\n"
"  \\item 5 VPs for bringing the Grail to your Faction Town \\textit{OR} 3 VPs for owning the Grail  at the end of the game.\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{King of the Hill} -- Start a map with a Dragon Utopia in the middle.\n"
"You don't need to fight the Level 7 Combat to capture it.\n"
"You get 1 VP for each Round you hold the Dragon Utopia under your control, no VPs from anything else.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/random_scenario.tex:35
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\textbf{Capture the Grail} -- Start a map with the Grail in the middle.\n"
"Standard Grail rules apply: spend 2 \\svg{movement} to dig it up, and bring it to your Town.\n"
"\\vspace*{\\fill}\n"
"\\columnbreak\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
